How did granddad pick up his news bulletins. Do not ask him for a clue because you just cannot miss the prompt in the picture. Another great gift idea that comes with dials knobs and sepia tone memories The retro radio can go on your bedside table Your mantelpiece Bookshelf or Work table. It needs pride of place and isolated from your new-fangled gadgets. This exquisite miniature is an accurate take-away from the vintage design classics. In the early days The cabinet was like any piece of well crafted furniture ? in fact it was the center piece in your drawing room. The look was heavy paneled with polished or painted finishes. Cabinet inlays had gold or Lighter wood as a set-off. The key focus points were the band spread and the all-important knobs Which were visual highlights with a functional purpose. All this is captured in this radio Which actually tells you the time ? the clock face here is positioned where you had normally find the band spread. The piece is made of high-quality mold metal parts with surface treatment and special effects - especially in terms of chrome and metallic finishes. If you buy this as a birthday gift here is an interesting way to make it radio-active. Set the alarm for midnight-twelve and gift wrap it with your card. The easily available Crystal battery (1 No.) is included. This is a display-only miniature and not a working piece. The quartz clock works beautifully.
